text: Kuyurgazy () is a rural locality (a village) in Yakshimbetovsky Selsoviet, Kuyurgazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 189 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 34 km from Yermolayevo, 8 km from Yakshimbetovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kuyurgazinsky District
title: Kuyurgazy
